# Database Migrations (Flyway)

## File Naming
- Versioned: `V{version}__{description}.sql` (e.g., `V1__create_users_table.sql`)
- Repeatable: `R__{description}.sql` (e.g., `R__refresh_views.sql`)
- Version format: `V1`, `V1.1`, `V1.1.1` -- monotonically increasing
- Double underscore `__` separates version from description

## Migration Rules
- Never modify an existing versioned migration after it has been applied
- New changes require new migration files
- Each migration should be idempotent where possible
- Include both DDL and seed data in separate migrations

## SQL Standards
- snake_case for table and column names
- Explicit `NOT NULL` constraints
- Always define primary keys
- Foreign keys with explicit names
- Index names: `idx_{table}_{columns}`

## Spring Boot Configuration
- `spring.flyway.enabled=true` (default with Flyway on classpath)
- `spring.flyway.locations=classpath:db/migration`
- Use `spring.flyway.baseline-on-migrate=true` for existing databases

## Testing
- Use Testcontainers for migration testing against real database engines
- Test both up-migration and rollback scripts

